It was imagined, that [p:Henry] had been strangled before the house was blown up. But this supposition is contradicted by the confession of the criminals; and there is no necessity to admit it in order to account for the condition of his body. There are many instances that men's lives have been saved who had been blown up in ships. Had [p:Henry] fallen on water he had not probably been killed.

