{#n48}
Some even of those who defend the queen's measures, allow that in ten years fifty priests were executed, and fifty-five banished. [p:Camden], p. 649.

{#n49}
Besides the petition after mentioned, another proof of the prevalency of the puritans among the commons was their passing a bill for the reverent observance of Sunday, which they termed the Sabbath, and the depriving the people of those amusements, which they were accustomed to take on that day. D'Ewes, p. 335. It was a strong symptom of a contrary spirit in the upper house, that they proposed to add Wednesday to the fast days, and to prohibit entirely the eating of flesh on that day. [D'Ewes, p. 373.]

{#n50}
